args: I won't be upset with you, Notte,\nbut you have to tell me the truth.
I AM telling the truth! It wasn't ME!
Hmm? Are Cleo and Notte arguing?
What's wrong, you two?\nDid something happen?
It seems SOMEONE has put a serious\ndent in our berry supply.
I was out of the kitchen for a little while,\nand when I returned, the berries had\nmysteriously grown legs and wandered off.
You love berries, don't you, Notte?\nAdmit it! It was you!
I told you, NO! You gotta trust me!
I'm not a big proponent of making\nemotionally-charged arguments based\non trust or the lack thereof.
Perhaps you might consider turning to\nthe world's most reliable tool: numbers.
What in the world does that mean?
Fortunately, this is the kitchen, so I think\nwe can just... Ah ha! Here it is.
A scale? Wait, are you gonna use that\nthing to prove I didn't eat the berries?
Correct! We are going to weigh you.
If we suppose that Notte ate the berries,\nher mass ought to have increased by a\ncommensurate amount.
That does seem like a way to establish\nthe truth with certainty.
It's redemption time for ol' Notte!\nC'mon, Xiao Lei, let's do this thing.
Er, wait. In order for this to work, don't we\nneed to know Notte's original weight?
Aw maaaan! I was THIS close to being\nable to rub it in Cleo's face.
But we do have Notte's original weight;\nI took it last night while she was sleeping.
In that case, we can just—HEY!\nWHAT THE HECK, MAN?!
I know I should have asked, but I've never\nhad a chance to determine the mass of\nan actual faerie before.
Well, if it gets me off the hook for this\nwhole berry thing, I guess I'll let it go.
Just so. Now, onto the scale. Hup!
Now we add the counterweights,\nand then... Hmm?
Your mass has increased since yesterday.
Whaaat?! No way! You made a mistake!
I didn't do it! It wasn't meee!\nC'mon, you gotta believe me!
I mean, I KNOW I like berries, and I DID\nhorf down a bunch of 'em for breakfast\nthis morning, but I DIDN'T steal any!
Ah! In that case, this could be weight\nyou gained from your breakfast.
Notte, I must know exactly how many\nberries you consumed this morning.
Umm...like, four? Maybe five?\nI wasn't exactly counting.

Then let us suppose you consumed four
and a half berries. If we assume the
average weight of a single berry based
on all of those which remain...
Right then! We now know the weight of\nyour breakfast. So if we subtract that\nfrom your current body mass...
She did not consume your missing berries.
YESSS! IN YOUR FACE, CLEO!\nOh, and thanks for the save, Xiao Lei.
But in that case, who DID eat the...
Er, did any of you hear that? It sounded\nlike it came from beneath the table.
Look at his mouth! Those are stains!\nBERRY stains!
Oh, crap! Uh, I mean...no they ain't!

And I've totally NOT been hidin'
under this table ever since Cleo
came back! I was just, uh...tryin'
to fix this wobbly leg! Yeah, that's it.
You are going to stand there and listen\nto me as I pelt you with invectives,\nand you are going to ENJOY IT.
Uh, Xiao Lei? Think maybe ya can\nuse that weighin' trick on me?
I refuse to use my beautiful numbers in\nan attempt to back up your pathetic lies.
Now sit still and listen to Cleo's lecture!
